{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1120,"text":"[Yoruba: Freeborn Ijebu-Ode son,]"},{"time":4920,"text":"[of true Ogbogbo Clan,]"},{"time":9640,"text":"[whose wealth and resources\nsurpass all that Europe ever had,]"},{"time":12640,"text":"[whose altar is filled with gold.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":18360,"text":"This chant is called the oríkì."},{"time":20600,"text":"My grandmother used to sing it\nto me when I was a child in Nigeria."},{"time":26000,"text":"See, an oríkì is the song of praise\nof the Yoruba people,"},{"time":29240,"text":"and this particularly speaks\nof treasures that the West does not have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34840,"text":"Mama -- that's what\nI call my grandmother --"},{"time":36960,"text":"told me many stories\nabout Yoruba mythology."},{"time":40000,"text":"You see, the Yorubas are an ethnic group\nfrom the southwestern part of Nigeria,"},{"time":43960,"text":"and I was always fascinated\nby these stories."},{"time":46120,"text":"I was always intrigued."},{"time":47920,"text":"And Yoruba culture has inspired\nmy art since I was a child."},{"time":51440,"text":"You see, African art is not just what\nyou buy at Harlem markets in New York."},{"time":55520,"text":"Every artist has a name,"},{"time":58600,"text":"and every artist has a story."},{"time":60680,"text":"This is my story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63640,"text":"See, mama had tattoos\non her arms and her legs."},{"time":67280,"text":"As a child, I thought\nshe was born with them,"},{"time":69560,"text":"with beautiful black lines\nand detailed symbols."},{"time":72240,"text":"And then she told me"},{"time":73520,"text":"that they were actually symbols\nfrom the Yoruba mythology."},{"time":77320,"text":"I never knew how this was going\nto influence the artist that I am today."},{"time":81520,"text":"You see, as a young child,\nI saw art everywhere."},{"time":83960,"text":"I remember the house we lived in\nin Ilorin, in Stadium Road."},{"time":87720,"text":"We had marble floors,"},{"time":89320,"text":"and you know, I would look\nat the marble floors,"},{"time":91920,"text":"and I would see all sorts\nof patterns and designs in it,"},{"time":94600,"text":"and I thought everybody could see them."},{"time":96520,"text":"So I would call my brother,\nand I would be like,"},{"time":98800,"text":"\"Ikeolu, come and see this marble design,\nsee this pattern, see this mask.\""},{"time":102360,"text":"And he would tell me,\n\"Laolu, I don't see anything.\""},{"time":104840,"text":"So I would use ink, and I would trace out\nwhat I saw on the floor."},{"time":107960,"text":"And then when my mom noticed,\nshe got really upset."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":112160,"text":"But that didn't stop me."},{"time":113440,"text":"I switched from ink to chalk,"},{"time":115120,"text":"because I got in trouble a lot\nwith my teachers and my parents."},{"time":118120,"text":"So I remember my mom said,\n\"Laolu, we are Christians."},{"time":121040,"text":"Why don't you draw like other people?"},{"time":122880,"text":"Why don't you draw landscapes\nor maybe you draw chairs or furniture,"},{"time":127200,"text":"or maybe even draw Jesus?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":129400,"text":"You know, I could paint\nthe whole house if I had a chance,"},{"time":132160,"text":"but when I grew up,\nI knew being an artist was not an option,"},{"time":135120,"text":"so I wanted to be the person\nmy parents wanted me to be,"},{"time":138120,"text":"so I went to law school."},{"time":139720,"text":"Of course, that's my dad there.\nHe was so proud that day."},{"time":143520,"text":"And this was what my notebooks\nlooked like in law school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":149440,"text":"Of course I would miss classes,"},{"time":150970,"text":"and I would make up excuses\nwhy I wasn't going to class."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155160,"text":"But when I started working\nat the Human Rights Commission"},{"time":157880,"text":"as a human rights attorney,"},{"time":159240,"text":"my mind was elsewhere."},{"time":161320,"text":"I saw a very tough reality."},{"time":164120,"text":"I worked with children"},{"time":165400,"text":"who had to choose\nbetween getting an education"},{"time":168240,"text":"and actually being forced into marriage."},{"time":170960,"text":"I was so frustrated\nseeing all the injustice around me,"},{"time":174560,"text":"and my only outlet was art,"},{"time":176160,"text":"so I started painting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178160,"text":"This piece is called \"Dreamscape.\""},{"time":180040,"text":"So when you zoom into this piece,"},{"time":181680,"text":"you're going to see a girl child"},{"time":184080,"text":"and the accidental birth,"},{"time":185960,"text":"the fact that our future\nis controlled by where we are born."},{"time":191320,"text":"Now, the next one you see\na man and a man holding hands,"},{"time":195120,"text":"a woman and a woman holding hands."},{"time":197000,"text":"You see, in Nigeria,\nsame-sex relationship is criminalized."},{"time":201160,"text":"You can actually get 14 years for that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203680,"text":"With my art, I like to tell stories."},{"time":205720,"text":"Through my art,\nI like to start a conversation."},{"time":207960,"text":"So in this one, you see the map of Africa,"},{"time":210200,"text":"you see the questions, you see crying,"},{"time":212080,"text":"and there you see syringes\nplugged into Africa"},{"time":214280,"text":"and the natural resources\nbeing drained out."},{"time":216400,"text":"So I asked myself, where does it go?"},{"time":218960,"text":"Who benefits from all of this?"},{"time":221640,"text":"You see, with my art,"},{"time":222920,"text":"the way I weave my art around\nthe patterns, the masks, the stories,"},{"time":226800,"text":"and the way I use my lines,"},{"time":228160,"text":"it's all from the Yoruba culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229920,"text":"So in 2013, I made a big gamble."},{"time":232480,"text":"I quit my job and I moved to New York City\nto practice art full time."},{"time":236840,"text":"Of course, my parents were like,"},{"time":238440,"text":"\"Oh, [it's just a phase.]\nHe'll come back.\""},{"time":241120,"text":"But life as an artist\nin New York was not easy,"},{"time":244120,"text":"because I was broke,"},{"time":246160,"text":"no money, no gallery agents,\nno representation,"},{"time":249120,"text":"so no gallery would show my work."},{"time":250760,"text":"So I thought to myself, I need to survive."},{"time":252920,"text":"So I started painting on clothes\nto make a living."},{"time":256519,"text":"I started painting on shoes."},{"time":258519,"text":"I started customizing things for people."},{"time":260839,"text":"And then soon I realized the power,"},{"time":262560,"text":"because people were so proud\nto wear their stories."},{"time":266240,"text":"So I started painting on everything."},{"time":268200,"text":"I painted on guitars,"},{"time":269760,"text":"I started doing murals,"},{"time":271000,"text":"anything I could find\nmy hand on I painted,"},{"time":273080,"text":"and everything became my canvas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274920,"text":"So one day, I was just going\non my Instagram feed,"},{"time":278240,"text":"and I saw this picture."},{"time":279720,"text":"It was Reign. She took a picture\nstanding in front my art,"},{"time":282840,"text":"and the moment I saw that photo,"},{"time":284600,"text":"something happened in that moment."},{"time":286280,"text":"I could actually see my artwork\ngo into her and come out of her literally,"},{"time":290720,"text":"and that's how I started painting\non human bodies."},{"time":294920,"text":"As a child I saw art on the marble floors,"},{"time":297800,"text":"I saw art on walls,"},{"time":299440,"text":"but now I see art on people's faces\nand people's bodies."},{"time":302920,"text":"I remember my grandmother,"},{"time":304960,"text":"and I realized that\nmost of my creative instincts"},{"time":307840,"text":"were actually based\non my childhood memories"},{"time":310920,"text":"and the art on my grandmother's skin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313320,"text":"Now I look at all the people I painted,\nand I think to myself, like,"},{"time":316560,"text":"what would it look like\nif we all walked around"},{"time":318800,"text":"like gods and goddesses\nfrom Yoruba mythology?"},{"time":321000,"text":"And boom, that's how\nThe Sacred Art of the Ori was born."},{"time":323800,"text":"You see, Ori in Yoruba mythology"},{"time":326320,"text":"means your soul, it means your essence,\nit means your instincts."},{"time":329400,"text":"And I realized that only\nwhen you tap into your Ori,"},{"time":331920,"text":"then you can actually move mountains."},{"time":334480,"text":"So there's something so immediate\nabout painting on human bodies."},{"time":339640,"text":"It's like art in motion."},{"time":342480,"text":"It's like a 3D experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344560,"text":"So one day, I was just doing\nmy regular work in Brooklyn,"},{"time":349360,"text":"and I got an email that said,"},{"time":351080,"text":"\"Hi, I'm a big fan of your work."},{"time":353400,"text":"Would you like to paint\nfor my music video?"},{"time":355441,"text":"Signed, Beyoncé.\""},{"time":356720,"text":"Like, Beyoncé emailed me."},{"time":358200,"text":"I was like, what?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":359560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":361240,"text":"I was like, what,\nhow did she even know me?"},{"time":363320,"text":"I thought this can't be true.\nOf course I thought it was a scam."},{"time":366360,"text":"The Nigerian in me was like, nah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":369240,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":371400,"text":"But incredibly enough,\nit was real, it was true,"},{"time":373880,"text":"and things happened really fast."},{"time":375480,"text":"You see, Beyoncé wanted\nto pay homage to New Orleans,"},{"time":378000,"text":"and my art reminded her\nof her creole origins."},{"time":381280,"text":"So when \"Lemonade\" dropped, of course,"},{"time":383640,"text":"boom, everything just went\nfrom zero to 100 real fast."},{"time":388200,"text":"People featured me in magazines,"},{"time":390600,"text":"interviews."},{"time":391840,"text":"People stopped me in the street."},{"time":393440,"text":"People knew my name, like --"},{"time":394920,"text":"And sometimes I had to step back"},{"time":396520,"text":"and just chill,\nand, like, take everything in."},{"time":399600,"text":"You know, as artists,\nwe work so hard all our lives"},{"time":402040,"text":"for our art to be recognized,"},{"time":403480,"text":"and for this I feel blessed."},{"time":405240,"text":"However, the attorney\nin me is still there,"},{"time":407320,"text":"so I use my art\nto fight for what I believe in."},{"time":411160,"text":"My Yoruba heritage is always there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413800,"text":"I'd like to share with you tonight\nsome of my art in motion."},{"time":418760,"text":"Please, welcome with me on stage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421120,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":422880,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":437360,"text":"Now, this is Geli, and this is Reign."},{"time":440800,"text":"These are the first two people\nI ever painted in my life,"},{"time":444120,"text":"and I spent the past day painting on them."},{"time":447880,"text":"Tonight, they represent\nmy hopes and my fears."},{"time":451960,"text":"Now, I put my fears on the back."},{"time":456840,"text":"I put my hopes in front."},{"time":460880,"text":"What are my hopes?"},{"time":464440,"text":"I hope that people know"},{"time":465720,"text":"that Africa is not just\none huge, nameless continent"},{"time":469960,"text":"that is all the same."},{"time":471560,"text":"I also hope that people know"},{"time":472960,"text":"that in Nigeria, we have\nover 350 ethnic groups and languages,"},{"time":478960,"text":"and I am just one artist from one of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481720,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":486400,"text":"I also hope that you know\nthat I hope I will be able to change"},{"time":489400,"text":"the way people talk about African art\non the continent and here,"},{"time":493400,"text":"and I hope you know that African art"},{"time":495160,"text":"is not just what you buy\nat Harlem markets in New York"},{"time":498680,"text":"and that every piece of art\nyou see has a story,"},{"time":501560,"text":"and every artist has a name."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503200,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504440,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}